### Health check (no auth -> unattributed session bucket)
GET http://localhost:4143/health

### Log in as Alice (JWT bearer; session = alice@example.com via the uid claim)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:4143/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "alice@example.com", "password": "wonderland" }

### Browse the catalog with Alice's token
GET http://localhost:4143/catalog
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### Add an item to Alice's cart
POST http://localhost:4143/cart/items
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": "p-1003", "qty": 1 }

### Place an order
POST http://localhost:4143/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### HTTP Basic operator (session = ops-admin)
GET http://localhost:4143/admin/metrics
Authorization: Basic b3BzLWFkbWluOm9wc3Bhc3M=

### Opaque API key (session = the key string, a service account)
GET http://localhost:4143/admin/metrics
Authorization: Bearer sk_live_billing_7f3a91

### A customer hitting admin -> 403 (colors the session error rate)
GET http://localhost:4143/admin/metrics
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### Broken product -> 500
GET http://localhost:4143/catalog/p-broken
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}
